FBIS3-1701 "drchi040_a_94019" FBIS-CHI-94-040 Document Type:Daily Report 1 March 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General Muslims Oppose Russian Peacekeepers Deployment in Sarajevo OW0103053294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0510 GMT 1 Mar 94 OW0103053294 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Belgrade, February 28 (XINHUA) -- Bosnian Muslim leader Alija Izetbegovic today expressed opposition to the deployment of Russian peacekeepers in Sarajevo, terming it as "a provocation that might lead to conflict." "We oppose the dispatch of Russian troops to Bosnia,...the decision should be canceled," he said. The presence of Russian troops in Sarajevo demonstrated Russian support for the Bosnian Serbs, Izetbegovic said in a letter to Yasushi Akashi, UN special envoy in former Yugoslavia. Meanwhile, Bosnian ambassador to the UN presented a similar letter to the Security Council.
